<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><title>My will</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 I'm setting the stage for the things I love
 I'm not now the man I once couldn't be
 Nothing on earth could now ever move me
 I now have a will and the strength a man needs

[V2]
 It's my will and I'm not moving
 'Cause if it's Your will then nothing can shape it
 It's my will to bow and praise You
 I now have a will to praise my God

[V3]
 Complexity haunts me for I am two men
 Entrenched in a battle that I'll never win
 My discipline fails me
 My knowledge it fools me
 But You are my shelter, the strength that I need

[V4]
 I'm learning to give up the rights to myself
 The bits and the pieces I've gathered as well
 It never compares to the joy that You bring me
 The peace that You show me
 Is the strength that I need

[V5]
 We've got to be children of peace
 We've got to be children of peace</lyrics>
<hymn_number>332</hymn_number>
<author>Evan Schoombie</author>
</song>